fields.description:
At the moment, we have the following endpoint:
{noformat}
/rest-service-fecru/admin/repositories/{repository}/permissions/groups
{noformat}
that allows us to update the repository permissions on a group basis. For completeness, it would be useful to have a similar call to be able to give individual users repository permissions, as is also permitted in the UI.

There should also ideally be a field as in {{"admin" = true}} , to give the User admin permissions on the repository.

h5. Problem 
JQL search for "P4 Job" returns wrong result after issue getting reindexed without user context due to permission check in {{getValueFromIssue()}} method


h5. Steps to Reproduce
# Setup Jira and FishEye instances.
# Setup application link between the two instances.
# Go to *Jira Administration* > *Issues* > *Custom Fields*.
# Select *Add Custom Field*, search for the *Job Checkbox* field and add it.
# In the screens configuration, select the screens for which you wish the Perforce Job checkbox to show up. Since the job is created upon the creation of an issue, you may select the following fields:
#* Default Screen
#* <PROJECT_KEY>: Simple Issue Tracking Create Issue Screen
# Click on *Update* to save the configuration.
# Create a new issue on Jira and select 'Yes' option under the newly created *Job Checkbox* field.
# Search the relevant issue with the following JQL query.
{code}"P4 Job" ~ "true"{code}
#* Check that JQL return proper result 
# Run Full Locked reindex 
# Run same JQL again 

h5. Expected Results
* _Job Checkbox_ custom field Lucene index value should be either {{true}} or {{false}} based on the custom field string value.
* JQL should return proper result 

h5. Actual Results
* _Job Checkbox_ custom field Lucene index value is changed to {{no_permission}}
* JQL doesn't return proper result.

h5. Notes
Whenever the user who does not have the *View development tools* permission, does issue update _Job Checkbox_ custom field Lucene index value is changed to {{no_permission}}.

Relevant Code:
{code}
public class JobSwitchCFType extends TextCFType
{
    public static final String WITHOUT_PERFORCE_JOB = "false";
    public static final String WITH_PERFORCE_JOB = "true";
    public static final String NO_PERMISSION = "no_permission";

   ...
    @Override
    public Object getValueFromIssue(CustomField customField, Issue issue)
    {
        if (permissionManager.hasPermission(SoftwareProjectPermissions.VIEW_DEV_TOOLS, issue.getProjectObject(),
                authenticationContext.getLoggedInUser()))
        {
            if (WITH_PERFORCE_JOB.equals(super.getValueFromIssue(customField, issue)))
                return WITH_PERFORCE_JOB;
            else
                return WITHOUT_PERFORCE_JOB;
        }
        else
        {
            return NO_PERMISSION;
        }
    }
{code}
Note: {{authenticationContext.getLoggedInUser()}} 

h5. Workaround
# Configure *View development tools* permission to *Anyone* on the associated permission scheme.
# Run project reindex to reindex affected issues
